# ğŸš Doshell Installation Guide

Doshell brings familiar DOS-style commands to modern Linux shells. Whether you're on WSL, Ubuntu, Fedora, or anything with Bash, Doshell helps bridge the muscle memory gap with intuitive aliases and enhancements.

## ğŸš€ Installation

Clone the repository:
  git clone https://github.com/twbaty/doshell.git
  cd doshell

Make the setup script executable and run it:
  chmod +x setup-doshell.sh
  ./setup-doshell.sh

Reload your shell:
  source ~/.bashrc  # or source ~/.zshrc

Verify installation by running:
  dir
  cls
  copy

